Despite the fact that {KGT:src} says the suffixes {-'egh:v} and {-moH:v} are generally used when giving commands with a verb describing a state, {yItamchoH!:sen} is in {TKD:src}, and MO has written {yIpIv!:sen} in a letter. Also, the KLI lists {yIDoghQo'!:sen} among its example Klingon phrases.

Canon violations of this rule include:
